Shekarau emerged the standard-bearer of the NNPP in a Senatorial primary election held at Gezawa, headquarters of Gezawa Local Government Area (LGA) of Kano State. Also Read: Nigeria’s Problems’ll Be Resolved With Kwankwaso As President – NNPP Chair Shekarau, a former governor of Kano State and a serving senator, defected from the All Progressives Congress (APC) to NNPP after failing to secure the party’s ticket for another term in the senate. He is now the unopposed candidate of the NNPP for the same position.